==English==
===Etymology===
French, from Italian [[macchietta]] ‘speck, little spot’, diminutive of [[macchia]] ‘spot’, ultimately from Latin [[maculare]] ‘spot, stain, maculate’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mæ'kɛt/

===Noun===
'''maquette'''
# a preliminary [[model]] or [[sketch]] used in preparation for making a [[sculpture]]
#:*'''1993''': His presence would be an affront to my body; so, for it, there would be the rare delight of extinguishing an imperfect and distressed version of itself, a prototype, a '''maquette'''. — Will Self, ''My Idea of Fun''

